          <h2>Unpacking and Initial Assembly</h2>
          <p>Systematic unpacking and assembly prevents losing components and establishes organized approach to telescope operation. Resist temptation to hastily assemble for immediate observing—investing 30-60 minutes in careful initial setup pays dividends through years of reliable use.</p>

          <h3>Inventory Check</h3>
          <p>Before discarding packaging, verify all components present by checking manufacturer's packing list. Typical telescope packages include: main optical tube assembly (OTA), mount (Dobsonian base, alt-azimuth tripod, or equatorial mount), tripod (if applicable), counterweights (for equatorial mounts), finder scope with mounting bracket, eyepieces (typically 2-3 included), diagonal (for refractors and catadioptrics), accessory tray, hand controller (for GoTo scopes), basic tools, and user manual.</p>

          <p>If components missing, contact retailer or manufacturer immediately—don't attempt operation with incomplete equipment. Save all packaging for at least 30 days in case return necessary. Photograph packaging configuration before unpacking valuable telescopes—documents proper packing method for future transport or potential returns.</p>

          <h3>Daytime Assembly</h3>
          <p>Perform initial assembly during daytime in well-lit area—attempting first-time assembly in darkness invites dropped components, missing fasteners, and frustration. Work on carpeted floor or padded surface protecting optics from accidental impacts. Have adequate workspace laying out all components systematically.</p>

          <p><strong>Dobsonian Assembly:</strong> Simplest telescope type. Attach altitude bearings to base board using included hardware (typically wing nuts or bolts requiring no tools). Place optical tube on bearings ensuring balance. Install finder scope in bracket on tube side. Insert eyepiece in focuser. Total time: 5-10 minutes.</p>

          <p><strong>Refractor on Alt-Azimuth Mount:</strong> Assemble tripod extending legs to stable height and spreading accessory tray securing leg separation. Attach mount head to tripod top using central bolt. Mount optical tube in tube rings or saddle plate on mount head. Install finder scope in mounting bracket on tube. Insert diagonal into focuser then eyepiece into diagonal. Total time: 15-20 minutes.</p>

          <p><strong>Reflector on Equatorial Mount:</strong> Most complex assembly. Assemble tripod and spread legs to stable position. Attach equatorial mount head to tripod using central bolt. Install counterweight shaft pointing downward. Slide counterweight(s) onto shaft and partially tighten. Mount optical tube in tube rings on declination axis. Balance tube by sliding in rings until balanced fore-aft. Attach finder scope. Install eyepiece in focuser. Total time: 30-45 minutes first time.</p>

          <p><strong>Computerized/GoTo Telescopes:</strong> Follow manufacturer assembly instructions precisely—motor alignment and cable routing critical for proper operation. Install batteries or connect power supply before testing motor functions. Perform "home position" initialization if required before first use. Total time: 20-40 minutes depending on complexity.</p>

          <h3>Pre-Use Inspection</h3>
